      "description": "Available now is a museum-quality 2004 BMW M3 (E46) in Laguna Seca Blue. This specimen is powered by the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six, featuring individual throttle bodies and a double-VANOS system that performs flawlessly. Power is delivered via a tactile Getrag 6-speed manual transmission to a factory M-Variable differential lock. The chassis remains rigid with zero subframe issues, and the suspension geometry is perfectly dialed to factory specifications. This vehicle boasts original paint with exceptional depth and an interior free of typical bolster wear or pixel degradation. A meticulously maintained example of analog performance engineering.",
